rComments: Good teacher, very hands on. Knows his stuff. Assignments were tough but doable. You'll learn a lot in the course

Great professor overall! He is technically strong and very experienced with real world applications of the theory we studied and hence I learned a lot under him. Further, he encourages having discussions in class.

I enjoyed the classes a lot but stopped attending them when I got busy with my other courses

rComments: Attendance isn't mandatory, but there are some things he only does in class (lecture notes have blanks, or code has blank sections) that forces you to go to class, unless of course, you choose to learn online instead. Assignments were okay, not too easy or too difficult.
CSC309. Good prof. Answers questions. Great notes - slides made available on line. Very useful course content (JavaScript, Struts, AJAX, REST).
Boring. Vague. Internet tutorials are better. A waste of your tuition dollars.
